24/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's President Branko Crvenkovski reiterated Friday (22 October) that the country would not pull out its troops from Iraq and remains committed to the anti-terror coalition. 
Crvenkovski's statement came a day after the Macedonian government confirmed the killings of three Macedonian construction workers by an Islamic militant group in Iraq. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 23/10/04; UPI - 22/10/04)
